translated: Enemund, Karl Martin Nalianiael, a high school teacher. Born on November 23rd, 1884 in Kumila. Married on the 27th to Siri Mathilda Fridholm. They had a daughter named Gunhild, born in 1929. Enemund completed his exams in Örebro in 1905, earned a Bachelor of Arts degree in Uppsala in 1913, completed a teaching internship for high school Latin in Gothenburg in 1917, and earned a teaching license in Gothenburg from 1932 to 1933. He worked as a teacher in various schools, including Kristinehamn's private gymnasium and middle school from 1918 to 1922, a substitute teacher in Härnösand from 1922 to 1923, in Östersund from 1923 to 1924, in Örnisköldsviik from 1924 to 1925, in Västerås from 1925 to 1929, then as a part-time teacher from 1929 to 1930, and a temporary teacher in Vänersborg from 1930 to 1931, in Skövde from 1931 to 1932, and as a part-time teacher in Skövde from 1933 to 1934. From 1934 to 1935, he taught at a private school in Gothenburg, then began teaching at Vara samrealskola in 1935, initially as a substitute teacher until 1938 when he became a permanent teacher. In 1947, he became an adjunct teacher in modern and German languages. He traveled to Tysikill in 1920, Norway in 1921 and 1924.
